data.enText: connected with goods that are bought and sold in large quantities, especially so they can be sold again to make a profit
happening or done to a very large number of people or things
the wholesale slaughter of innocent people

data.chText: 我们批量购买建筑材料。
data.enText: We buy the building materials wholesale.

data.chText: 这些年轻人因过量吸海洛因大批死亡。
data.enText: These young people die wholesale from heroin overdoses.

tr: the selling of goods to merchants
usually in large quantities for resale to consumers
on a large scale without careful discrimination

example: I can sell it to you wholesale

value.def: Wholesale is the activity of buying and selling goods in large quantities and therefore at cheaper prices, usually to shopkeepers who then sell them to the public.

example.ex: Warehouse clubs allow members to buy goods at wholesale prices...
example.tran: 仓储式会员店允许会员以批发价购买商品。

example.ex: I am in the wholesale trade.

value.def: If something is sold wholesale, it is sold in large quantities and at cheaper prices, usually to shopkeepers.

example.ex: The fabrics are sold wholesale to retailers, fashion houses, and other manufacturers.
example.tran: 这些纺织品被批发给零售商、时装店和其他制造商。

value.def: You use wholesale to describe the destruction, removal, or changing of something when it affects a very large number of things or people.

example.ex: They are only doing what is necessary to prevent wholesale destruction of vegetation...
example.tran: 他们只是在采取必要措施避免大规模的植被破坏。

example.ex: It was wholesale slaughter of women and children.
example.tran: 那是对妇女和儿童的大规模屠杀。

example.ex: ...a government which kills wholesale and guerrillas who kill selectively.
example.tran: 实行大规模杀戮的政府和有选择地杀人的游击队

trans: 银行批发业务，批发银行业
